Joe Biden is being inaugurated as the 46th President of the United States of America. Biden served as deputy president of the US during the Barack Obama administration following years of service in the American government. Biden won the United States elections against President Donald Trump. Trump, who disputed the presidential election results, has opted not to attend Bidenâ€™s presidential inauguration. Biden won the elections after receiving the highest electoral votes as well as the popular vote. He received over 75 million following a high voter turnout as the Republican Party battled the Democratic Party to retain power. Kamala Harris becomes the first female Vice President of the US.      